  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-5">
      <h2>Step 2 - Create a Session</h2>
      <p>All observation sessions are associated with a student record.  <span class="highlight-red">A student can have many sessions associated with his or her account</span>.  To create a session, a user must complete the create session form. In this form, the session setting, session task, number of intervals, and length of intervals (in seconds) are required. In addition, a total session time calculator is provided at the bottom of this form for the user's convenience. It is recommended that at least 40 intervals be measured at 15-second intervals to ensure that the data is valid and reliable.  There are two ways in which to create a session:</p>
      <h3>Create Session - Option 1</h3>
      <p>First, you can view the record of the student whom you wish to observe. Then, select the "Create Session" button below the student record (as indicated in the image).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-5">
      <div class="tutorial-image-container">
        <p class="image-caption">Create Session - Option 1</p>
        <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/13546265/25742308/d739d02a-315c-11e7-89de-74d61990e920.png" alt="Create Session Option 1">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-5">
      <h3>Create Session - Option 2</h3>
      <p>The second option is to go to the Student Record homepage where all student records are listed. Then, two additional steps are required:</p>
      <p>First, click on the "Create Sessions" button (Option 2 - Part A).</p>
      <p>After you complete this task, you will see a page which offers two options. The first is to create a student, which is required if there is no student record created for the individual you will be observing. However, if a student record already exists,
        you can click "Existing Student". This displays a list of all student records. From here, simply click "Select Student" from the row of the student whom you will be observing (Option 2 - Part B).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-5">
