  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-5">
      <h3>Time Interval Indicators</h3>
      <p>There are two indicators for time remaining in a given interval. The first lists the number of seconds remaining before the response is recorded. The second is a time bar which decreases in size as the interval comes to an end. This bar also changes
        color from green to red depending on the time remaining in an interval.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-5">
      <div class="tutorial-image-container">
        <p class="image-caption">Need Image</p>
        <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/13546265/25744197/8a9fa212-3166-11e7-8466-2c162d69f5ae.png" alt="Time Interval Indicators">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-5">
      <h3>Target Student vs. Random Peer Indicators</h3>
      <p>BOSS requires that a random peer be observed every 5th interval. There are two indicators to help the observer montor which student to observe. First, either "Observing: Target Student" or "Observing: Random Peer" will appear above the timer countdown.
        In addition, <span class="highlight-red">the background color changes to orange
        when a random peer is the individual being observed during an interval</span>. This decreases the likelihood that the observer will make an error in observing the wrong student.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-5">
      <div class="tutorial-image-container">
        <p class="image-caption">Need Image</p>
        <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/13546265/25744197/8a9fa212-3166-11e7-8466-2c162d69f5ae.png" alt="Target vs. Random Peer Indicators">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-5">
      <h3>Updating the Last Submission</h3>
      <p>If an error is made by the observer when recording the observed behavior, the user can update the previous interval's submission.</p>
      <p class="underline-h">Desktop Versions</p>
      <p>Updating he previous interval's enry can be accomplished by clicking the "edit" button for the last submission table. At this point, the observer
        can check a box if a behavior was observed, or uncheck a box if the behavior was not observed.  <span class="highlight-red">In order for the update to be saved, he observer must click the "submit" button
        below he update form</span>.</p>
      <p class="underline-h">Mobile Version</p>
      <p>Updating the last entry on a phone or table requires a user to click the
      "Edit Last Submission" button.  When clicked, a dropdown will appear and the observer can update the last entry by selecting or deselecting a box.  Please note
      that <span class="highlight-red">an observer must click the "Submit" button in order for the update to be saved</span>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-5">
      <div class="tutorial-image-container">
        <p class="image-caption">Updating a Submission</p>
        <img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/13546265/25744197/8a9fa212-3166-11e7-8466-2c162d69f5ae.png" alt="Updating a Submission">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-5">
      <h3>Nothing Selected Warning</h3>
      <p>The web application warns a user if an interval was submitted without any category being selected.  The warning differs depending on whether the observer is using the desktop or mobile version.</p>
      <p class="underline-h">Desktop Versions</p>
      <p>If an interval ends without at least one category being selected, <span class="highlight-red">the background of the last entry table turns red</span>. This increases the likelihood that an observe will notice that nothing was submitted for a previous interval. If this occurs, the observer can update the last submission as described above.</p>
      <p class="underline-h">Mobile Version</p>
      <p>For the mobile version, the user is notified by the color of the button for updating the last submission.  Specifically, <span class="highlight-red">the "Edit Last Submission" button turns red</span>.  If this occurs, the observer can update the last submission as described above.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-0 col-sm-5">
